Thailand Stocks: G Steel, Indorama, Thai Airways, Sri Trang

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-03-08T10:13:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/thailand-stocks-g-steel-indorama-thai-airways-sri-trang.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Thailand trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index rose 15.63, or 1.6 percent, to 1,018.57, the
highest close since Jan. 20.    G Steel Pcl (GSTEEL)  , Thailand’s second-biggest steel
maker by capacity, climbed 6.9 percent to 0.78 baht, its highest
close since October 2008, as trading resumed following a March 2
suspension. ArcelorMittal, the world’s biggest steelmaker, plans
to buy a 40 percent stake for about $250 million, providing the
Thai company cuts debt, ArcelorMittal and G Steel said March 2.    Indorama Ventures Pcl (IVL)  , a chemical producer, jumped
7.6 percent to 49.5 baht, the highest close since Jan. 7. The
company was rated “outperform” in new coverage at Credit
Suisse Group AG, which said in a report to investors that the
company’s strengths are its “aggressive” growth plan and
“successful” track record in past acquisitions.    Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  , the largest publicly
traded rubber producer, gained 2.7 percent to 29 baht, the most
in a week. The company doubled its cash dividend to 1.25 baht a
share from a 0.60 baht per piece payout a year earlier.    Sino-Thai Engineering & Construction Pcl (STEC)  , a
construction company, rose 3.9 percent to 13.2 baht, the most
since Feb. 8. The share-price estimate was raised to 21 baht
from 19 baht at CLSA Asia Pacific Markets, which cited increased  government spending  on infrastructure.    Thai Airways International Pcl (THAI)  , the country’s
largest carrier, advanced 3.1 percent to 41.25 baht, the highest
since Feb. 17. Crude oil in  New York  fell for the first time in
three days.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
